\par <#/>"I think we have been tolerant enough... <#/>Those concerned, wake up and rectify the situation before it is too late," he told participants of a district environment meeting which included representatives of the 22 major industries at Thika.
\par <#/>D.K. Mundia, mayor of the town, then ordered a stop to the dumping of harmful solid wastes at Kang'oki, the municipality's main refuse disposal site to the east of Thika.
\par <#/>Mundia instructed tannery and tobacco processing plants to manage their waste materials within their resources. <#/>Medical institutions and private clinics were also told to dispose their toxic and infectious waste without polluting the environment.

